==Awards and honours==
{{BLP unsourced section|date=September 2014}}
* 1982: Nelly Award: Outstanding Writing, ''SCTV Comedy Network''
* 1983: [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing for a Variety Series#Outstanding Writing in a Variety or Music Program 2|Emmy Award for Outstanding Writing in a Variety or Music Program]], ''SCTV Comedy Network'' 
* 1993: [[Outer Critics Circle Award]]: Outstanding Actor in a Musical, ''[[The Goodbye Girl (musical)|The Goodbye Girl]]''
* 1993: Theater World Award
* 1993: Nominated for [[Tony Award for Best Actor in a Musical]]
* 1994: Member of the [[Order of Canada]]
* 1995: Earl Grey Lifetime Achievement Award
* 1999: [[Outer Critics Circle Award]]: Outstanding Actor in a Musical, ''[[Little Me (musical)|Little Me]]''
* 1999: [[Tony_Award_for_Best_Actor_in_a_Musical#1990s|Tony Award for Best Actor in a Musical]], ''Little Me''
* 2000: [[Canada's Walk of Fame]]
* 2002: [[Queen Elizabeth II Golden Jubilee Medal]]
* 2010: Nominated for [[62nd_Primetime_Emmy_Awards#Supporting_performances|Emmy Awards for Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Drama Series]], ''[[Damages (TV series)|Damages]]''
* 2010: Nominated for [[15th Satellite Awards#Best Supporting Actor in a Series.2C Miniseries.2C or Television Film|Satellite Awards for Best Actor in a Supporting Role in a Series]], ''[[Damages (TV series)|Damages]]''
* 2011: Nominated for [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Performer In An Animated Program#2010s|Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Performer In An Animated Program]], ''[[The Cat in the Hat Knows a Lot About That!]]''
* 2012: [[Queen Elizabeth II Diamond Jubilee Medal]]

